column5: DNR Still seeing knuckleheads here falsely saying that the company increasing its Authorized Shares is automatic dilution How can people trading stocks or investing be so ignorant about how share structures work Increasing the Authorized Shares AS is not dilution Increasing the Issued and Outstanding Shares OS is dilution A company increases its Authorized Shares for many reasons and not just to immediately dilute A company can have a Billion shares in its AS and only 500 million in its OS
